# MediNet: Getting Started
  
MediNet is a decentralized medical management system built on the Pi Network blockchain. It provides a secure and transparent platform for managing medical records, appointments, and billing. This guide will help you get started with MediNet.

# Prerequisites
  
Before you begin, make sure you have the following:

1. A computer with at least 4GB of RAM and 10GB of free disk space
2. A stable internet connection
3. A Pi Network account with at least 1 Pi coin

# Installation
  
1. Clone the MediNet repository from GitHub:

```
1. git clone https://github.com/KOSASIH/MediNet-PiNetworkBlockchainMedicalManagement.git
```
  
2. Install Node.js and npm:

```
sudo apt-get install nodejs npm
```
  
3. Install the Pi Network blockchain:

```
sudo apt-get install pi-blockchain
```
  
4. Install the MediNet dependencies:

```
1. cd MediNet-PiNetworkBlockchainMedicalManagement
2. npm install
```
  
5. Start the MediNet server:

```
npm start
```
  
6. Configuration
  
Create a .env file in the root directory of the project and add the following:

```
1. PI_NETWORK_USERNAME=<your Pi Network username>
2. PI_NETWORK_PASSWORD=<your Pi Network password>
3. PI_NETWORK_HOST=<your Pi Network host>
4. PI_NETWORK_PORT=<your Pi Network port>
5. Set the PI_NETWORK_HOST and PI_NETWORK_PORT to the address and port of your Pi Network node.

# Usage
  
1. Open a web browser and navigate to http://localhost:3000.
2. Log in with your Pi Network account.
3. Use the MediNet dashboard to manage medical records, appointments, and billing.

# Troubleshooting
  
If you encounter any issues, check the MediNet documentation and support forums.

# Additional Resources
- MediNet Documentation
- Pi Network Documentation
- Pi Network Support Forums

This guide should help you get started with MediNet. If you have any questions or issues, please refer to the MediNet documentation and support forums.  
